{"id":"sumpkin-griddle-cakes","name":"Sumpkin Griddle Cakes","unlisted":false,"tags":["breakfast","pancakes","pan"],"type":"staple","source":"Aegaeon's Refined Cuisine","rarity":2,"timeInMinutes":30,"prepInMinutes":10,"image":{"sources":{"webp":[{"src":"/_app/immutable/assets/main.Cix_2mj9.webp","w":600},{"src":"/_app/immutable/assets/main.mfTv6G5r.webp","w":1600}],"png":[{"src":"/_app/immutable/assets/main.BJcbNq27.png","w":600},{"src":"/_app/immutable/assets/main.rpSgra38.png","w":1600}]},"fallback":{"src":"/_app/immutable/assets/main.rpSgra38.png","w":1600,"h":800},"alt":"Sumpkin Griddle Cakes"},"description":"Pumpkin-infused pancakes with a hint of vanilla.","ingredients":[{"name":"All Ingredients","ingredients":[{"name":"Flour","type":"Grain","rarity":1,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":2,"denominator":1},"unit":"cups"}},{"name":"Baking Powder","type":"Grain","rarity":1,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":2,"denominator":1},"unit":"teaspoons"}},{"name":"Baking Soda","type":"Grain","rarity":2,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":1},"unit":"teaspoons"}},{"name":"Salt","type":"Spice","rarity":1,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":2},"unit":"teaspoons"}},{"name":"Ground Cinnamon","type":"Spice","rarity":2,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":2,"denominator":1},"unit":"teaspoons"}},{"name":"Nutmeg","type":"Spice","rarity":2,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":1},"unit":"teaspoons"}},{"name":"Pumpkin Puree","type":"Vegetable","rarity":3,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":15,"denominator":1},"unit":"oz can"}},{"name":"Brown Sugar","type":"Spice","rarity":2,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":3},"unit":"cups"}},{"name":"Egg","type":"Meat","rarity":1,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":1},"unit":"quantity"}},{"name":"Vegetable Oil","type":"Oil","rarity":1,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":3,"denominator":1},"unit":"tablespoons"}},{"name":"Whole Milk","type":"Liquid","rarity":1,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":3,"denominator":2},"unit":"cups"}},{"name":"Vanilla Extract","type":"Spice","rarity":2,"measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":1},"unit":"tablespoons"}}]}],"directions":{"steps":[{"description":"In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Set aside.","ingredients":[{"name":"Flour","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":2,"denominator":1},"unit":"cups"}},{"name":"Baking Powder","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":2,"denominator":1},"unit":"teaspoons"}},{"name":"Baking Soda","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":1},"unit":"teaspoons"}},{"name":"Salt","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":2},"unit":"teaspoons"}},{"name":"Cinnamon","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":2,"denominator":1},"unit":"teaspoons"}},{"name":"Nutmeg","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":1},"unit":"teaspoons"}}]},{"description":"In another bowl, blend the pumpkin, brown sugar, egg, oil, milk, and vanilla extract. Make sure it is well mixed and smooth, at least 1 minute stirring vigorously.","ingredients":[{"name":"Pumpkin Puree","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":15,"denominator":1},"unit":"oz"}},{"name":"Brown Sugar","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":3},"unit":"cups"}},{"name":"Egg","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":1},"unit":"quantity"}},{"name":"Vegetable Oil","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":3,"denominator":1},"unit":"tablespoons"}},{"name":"Whole Milk","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":3,"denominator":2},"unit":"cups"}},{"name":"Vanilla Extract","measure":{"amount":{"numerator":1,"denominator":1},"unit":"tablespoons"}}]},{"description":"Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and whisk gently to combine. The batter should be thick and lumpy.","ingredients":[]},{"description":"Heat a gridle or skillet over medium heat (about 375°F, 190°C). Coat with butter or nonstick cooking spray.","ingredients":[]},{"description":"Once hot, drop a large spoonful (1/4 cup) of batter onto the griddle; you can cook as many of these spoonfuls at a time as your pan allows. Cook until holes in the pancake surface start to form around the border, about 2-3 minutes. Then, flip the pancakes and cook on the other side another 1-2 minutes. Repeat until the batter is exhausted.","ingredients":[]},{"description":"Serve with other breakfast items, like fresh fruit, scrambled eggs, or sausages!","ingredients":[]}]},"gameIngredients":{"Sumpkin":3,"Weeping Flour":2,"Dawn Hygrangea":2},"interpretation":"<p>Griddle Cakes are pancakes, and the ingredients are consistent with that: all-purpose flour as weeping flour, and vanilla as dawn hygrangea (since hygrangeas are flowers and vanilla comes from flowers).</p><p>Sumpkins are what make this recipe unique. We use pumpkin puree to create an autumn-flavored pancake. Experiment with the spices, and give this Gormotti breakfast dish a try!</p>","references":[{"name":"Pumpkin Pancakes by Sally's Baking","href":"https://sallysbakingaddiction.com/pumpkin-pancakes-recipe/"}]}